===Etymology===
From {{inh|en|enm|nexte}}, {{m|enm|nexste}}, {{m|enm|nixte}}, from {{inh|en|ang|nīehsta}}, {{m|ang|nīehste}}, etc., inflected forms of {{m|ang|nīehst|t=nearest, next}}, superlative form of {{m|ang|nēah||nigh, near}}, corresponding to {{inh|en|gem-pro|*nēhwist|t=nearest, closest}}; equivalent to {{suffix|en|nigh|est}}. Cognate with {{cog|stq|naist|t=next}}, {{cog|nl|naast|t=next}}, {{cog|de|nächst|t=next}}, {{cog|da|næste|t=next}}, {{cog|sv|näst|t=next}}, {{cog|is|næst|t=next}}, {{cog|fa|نزد|tr=nazd|t=near, with}}.

